text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!Why should “saudade” be added into the Oxford English Dictionary?%0a%0a:Author: nbraga%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aThe word "saudade" should not be added to the OED because it doesn't have widespread use in the English-speaking world%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0a“Saudade” is a word that comes from the Portuguese language that is used “to explain the feeling of missing something or someone. It is used to talk about something that you used to have (and liked) but don't have anymore.” (1) It expresses the feelings of wistfulness, nostalgia, and longing. (2)%0a%0aThis word is widely used in Brazil and by Brazilians immigrants around the world. %0aIt is frequently used by immigrants when referring to things they used to have or do in their hometown. Due to its complexity, this word does not have a simple translation to the English language. So, it would be only fair to be%0aimplemented into the Oxford dictionary.%0a%0aHowever, according to the three criteria presented in the podcast: “widespread use, sustained use, and having a meaning;” this word would most likely not make it to the Oxford English Dictionary (4). To support this claim, the Corpus of Contemporary American English shows that the word “saudade” had a%0afrequency of only 23 (3). Although “saudade” has a deep meaning to those who use it, it would not be a strong enough argument to be added into the OED.%0a%0a(1) https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=saudade%0a(2) https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/saudade%0a(3) https://www.english-corpora.org/coca/%0a(4) Podcast%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: :)%0a(:Category: FunWithWords:)%0a(:Title: Why should “saudade” be added into the Oxford English Dictionary?:)
